stomers with processing transaction requests Provide high priority transaction support for specific customers, and other internal departments Provide and process appropriate solutions to transaction and funds related questions and request Act as a general-knowledge resource for the role as well a resource for operational requests Experience: Minimum of 2 years operational/financial employment Minimum of 1 year of employment in the digital asset space Background and understanding of securities, assets, funds processing, and book entry Prior knowledge about digital assets, blockchain, and wallets Prior knowledge about operational departments in financial companies Prior understanding of movement of funds related to wires and ACH's Skills: Communicates well with peers, colleagues (including leadership), and clients on a regular basis Demonstrate ability to confidently explain processes related to transactions to peers, colleagues, clients, and external businesses Must have an understanding of how cap tables and book-entry recording systems function, as well as banking portals. Possess prior knowledge of executing trades Must understand how blockchain functions as an ecosystem, and how to process digital asset transactions Must be able to identify constraint, bottlenecks, and potential problems for a variety of internal and external processes, with little to no clear resolution Consistent in taking ownership of problems, while providing a solution with appropriate documentation/explanation Ability to address details specific to individual tasks, as well as understanding the big picture associated with the task Able to address conflicts internally and externally related to direct ownership of tasks/processes Must have the ability to plan personal timeline to meet specific task goals Understand the requirements to be organized and work in an organized fashion Works efficiently with a pre-defined schedule or set of existing priorities but can also effectively prioritize situations and emergencies Works well independently and in group settings Demonstrate ability to communicate and work accordingly with other departments, and external businesses Able to stay focused and maintain drive throughout a busy and heavy workflow Self-motivated, and understands what needs to be done without requiring constant supervision Education Bachelors degree or higher is preferred Other Requirements: Eligible candidates will be asked to take a short quiz Working Conditions This job is based in our corporate offices in Las Vegas, Nevada. Culture is energetic, interactive, and growth oriented, far more of a fin tech environment than a traditional financial institution Job Type: Full-time position Salary: $45,000 - $50,000 annually (DOE) Benefits Flexible PTO/Paid holidays/Health, Dental, and Vision insurance for employee and dependents, which is currently 100% paid by the company, after the first day of the month following 60-days of employment/cell phone reimbursement up to $100 per month Job Type: Full-time Pay: $45,000.00 - $50,000.00 per year Experience: financial employment: 2 years (Preferred) operational: 2 years (Preferred) employment in digital asset space: 1 year (Preferred) Education: Bachelor's (Preferred) Work Location: One location Benefits: Health insurance Dental insurance Vision insurance Paid time off This Company Describes Its Culture as: Detail-oriented -- quality and precision-focused Outcome-oriented -- results-focused with strong performance culture Stable -- traditional, stable, strong processes People-oriented -- supportive and fairness-focused Team-oriented -- cooperative and collaborative Schedule: Monday to Friday Company's website: www.primetrust.com Benefit Conditions: Waiting period may apply Only full-time employees eligible Work Remotely: No ", 
